cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a neural network method for predicting CPU utilization of virtual machines in the cloud. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically involves time series analysis (cs.ST) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the importance of resource allocation in cloud computing (cs.DC) and the empirical analysis is based on Microsoft Azure's VM workloads (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing for text-based data preprocessing (cs.CL).
